snippet.title: My Response To Fatphobia Claims
snippet.description:
I was scrolling through reddit today and came across this post saying I have “fatphobic tendencies”. This was really hard for me to read and caused me to take a critical look back at my previous comments regarding obesity, bariatric treatments, and diet recommendations (Keto, intermittent fasting, vegan, etc.) Our culture demonizes people for their weight, from rogue marketing pushing “ideal bodies” in media to a lack of representation for large bodied people on stage and on screen. That being said, I am a doctor, and my job is to help people live longer, healthier lives, and often those results can be achieved through a variety of tactics that will reduce the weight of people who suffer from obesity. It’s a fine line between helping my patients and making sure they don’t feel judged or criticized for the way they look, and I’m working hard to get it right.

ORIGINAL REDDIT POST: https://www.reddit.com/r/antidiet/comments/hq0lfh/i_really_want_to_like_dr_mike_on_youtube_but_he/?sort=top

COMMENTS ON BARIATRIC SURGERY REDDITOR REFERS TO: 
https://youtu.be/rh2FFCQ7QSs?t=406

RESEARCH ON OBESITY AND WEIGHT IN REGARDS TO HEALTH:
https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK379120/
https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5704829/#:~:text=Bariatric%20surgery%20has%20proved%20to,LAGB)%2C%20reported%20inconsistent%20results
https://www.cochrane.org/CD003641/ENDOC_surgery-for-obesity
https://uihc.org/health-topics/how-effective-bariatric-surgery

MY APPEARANCE ON PHIL DEFRANCO’S SHOW DISCUSSING FAT SHAMING: https://youtu.be/IdPFaDt2dEo?t=1367

MY NUTRITION PLAYLIST: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLJRbJuI_csVAMq2VPr96h6TL4Y98rfznM

snippet.title: Naya Rivera's Ex Ryan Dorsey 'Can't Imagine' Raising Son Without Her
snippet.description:
As Naya Rivera's family, friends and fans continue to mourn her death, her ex-husband Ryan Dorsey is also struggling with the news. PEOPLE magazine reports that the actor, who shares 4-year-old son Josey with the late "Glee" star, has barely slept since her disappearance. "It's just a nightmare," a source said. "Although he wasn't with Naya, it's Josey's mom. Josey needs his mom. Ryan can't imagine raising [him] without Naya. It's the most devastating situation."

snippet.title: CARA IS PREGNANT!!!
snippet.description:
WOW! Cara is pregnant! Completely unexpected surprise pregnancy. For Gemma and the Triplets we tried for a year with no success, and later found out she has PCOS and doesn't ovulate correctly, so she got medical help and took a pill (letrozole) to help her ovulate and it did the trick for both pregnancies. We figured that if we wanted to get pregnant again she would have to go on that pill again. We weren't opposed to having more kids, but definitely thought at least 2 years before she got back on it. So this came out of nowhere. We truly believe everything happens for a reason, and that this baby is supposed to be a part of our family. Those struggling with infertility, we have family members going through the same thing, and although we will never know why certain things happen, we just pray that you will still stay strong and positive. Never give up! We are so excited for baby number 5 to join us and so are the kids! Their reaction videos were all filmed prior to this since we have known for 3 weeks, and we will show those soon. The main question we have is will it be multiples again??? Twins? Another triplet pregnancy?! haha that would be absolutely insane, but you never what will happen around here anymore. Thanks for all the support you guys! We love each and every one of you!

snippet.title: The 1985 Effect
snippet.description:
The 1985 Effect - Now, saying that J. Cole was right might just be an understatement. 1985 by J. Cole is slowly over time becoming a reality many rappers are having to face. Lil Pump was of course the guy who the track was aimed at; but it's far from ''just a diss track''. 1985 is the guide for how your average young & popping rapper can avoid the pitfalls that come with being in that position. The effect is in fact - in full effect & both Lil Pump & Smokepurpp are the tangible proof. That's what I talk about. 

In this video I talk about the effect of 1985, by J. Cole.

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS | Arsenal 2-1 Liverpool | Premier League | Lacazette, Nelson, Mane
snippet.description:
We kept our European hopes alive with a morale-boosting victory against Liverpool on Wednesday night.

Coming into a game against the champions off the back of a north London derby defeat was hardly ideal preparation, but we delivered a gritty, backs-to-the-wall performance to claim the points after goals from Alex Lacazette and Reiss Nelson.

With Saturday’s Emirates FA Cup semi-final against Manchester City looming large, Mikel Arteta made five changes to his side but it was the visitors who dominated much of the first half.

Playing with the swagger of the Premier League’s top dogs, Liverpool pushed us back in our own half for long periods and it came as little surprise when they took the lead through Sadio Mane’s close-range finish.

But for all their dominance, the visitors could not extend their advantage and we made them pay the price when Lacazette took advantage of a Virgil van Dijk error to score.

We then benefitted from another Liverpool mistake when Allison played a pass straight to Lacazette, who found Nelson to slot home his first Premier League goal.

We would have expected a response from the Reds after the interval, and we got one with Emi Martinez soon called into action to make a close-range save from Mohamed Salah.

Liverpool continued to pile on the pressure, but for all their possession we were standing firm and making life difficult for them as the game reached its closing stages.

Mane had the best chance for the visitors late on when he got goal side of Ainsley Maitland-Niles but poked his shot wide, while Joe Willock had a very late opportunity but sliced wide from close range.

That was that, and we claimed a welcome three points. On to Wembley next.
